(367, 1, '2016-10-15 15:57:51', '2016-10-15 15:57:51', ' <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h1 class="brand-name text-center">History & culture</h1>\r\n        <hr />\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"> <img class="img-responsive img-border" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/Trevyr_20080514_0062.jpg" alt="Grosmont Church" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>The Welsh borders</h2>\r\n        <p>The Welsh borders have seen many of the famous and infamous episodes of British history. These have left a legacy of castles, churches and other historical sites across the local area:</p>\r\n        <div id="copybullets" class="wide">\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>The Three Castles – Grosmont, Skenfrith, White Castle</li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://www.caerleon.net/" target="blank">Roman site at Caerleon</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/raglan.html" target="blank">Raglan Castle</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://www.herefordcathedral.org/" target="blank">Hereford	Cathedral (home of Mappa Mundi)</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/llantho.html" target="blank">Llanthony Abbey</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/tintern.html" target="blank">Tintern Abbey</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://visitblaenavon.mobi/" target="blank">Blaenavon - World Heritage site (Industrial Revolution and Big Pit)</a></li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"> <img class="img-responsive img-border" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/trevyr_092203_0027.jpg" alt="Skenfrith Castle" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>Walking, History & culture</h2>\r\n        <p>Why not combine a little walking and some history? Trevyr Barn is a	stone''s throw from Offa''s Dyke and in the middle of the 32 km Three Castles walk (Grosmont, White Castle and Skenfrith) which, for the fit, can be completed in a long summer''s day. There are plenty of shorter variations, and we will be happy to help you plan.</p>\r\n        <p>In <a href="http://www.grosmont.org" target="blank">Grosmont</a>, St Nicolas Church, with its large medieval nave, was built	in the 13th Century as part of the supporting infrastructure for Grosmont Castle. There are plenty of other interesting churches nearby, and among the best are: Cwmyoy, Partrishow, Kilpeck and Abbey Dore.</p>\r\n        <p> The Village Alive Trust is a local charity which works to preserve our local heritage and history. It has restored some fascinating buildings and has created some short trails to help you explore. Check out their website <a href="http://www.villagealivetrust.org.uk" target="_blank" title="Village Alive Trust">here</a>.</p>\r\n        <p><a href="http://www.hayfestival.com/wales" target="blank">The Hay Literary Festival</a> is an internationally renowned cultural event. Throughout the year, there are plenty of local festivals to suit all interests, which celebrate the culture and heritage of Monmouthshire. Check <a href="http://www.festivalsinmonmouthshire.co.uk/index.html" target="_blank" title="Festivals in Monmouthshire">here</a> for some ideas.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>', 'History and Culture', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '74-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-15 15:57:51', '2016-10-15 15:57:51', '', 74, 'http://localhost:81/wordpress-trevrybarn/74-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(368, 1, '2016-10-15 15:58:57', '2016-10-15 15:58:57', '<div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h1 class="brand-name text-center">A year at Trevyr Barn</h1>\r\n        <hr />\r\n        <p>We really enjoy the changing seasons at Trevyr Barn. Here are some ideas for things you can see and do without going very far at all.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n          <div class="panel-heading">\r\n            <h2>Spring</h2>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="panel-body">\r\n            <div class="panel-body"><img src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/spring.jpg" alt="Spring at Trevyr" class="img-responsive img-left" />\r\n              <p>Go for one of the <a href="http://www.grosmont.org/tourism/walks//walks-around-grosmont" target="_blank" title="Nearby walks">Grosmont walks</a> and enjoy the wild flowers (celandines, anemones, wild garlic).</p>\r\n              <p>Walk to Llangatock Lingoed and enjoy some local cider at the Hunter''s Moon.</p>\r\n              <p>In late spring, enjoy cherry and apple blossom in the orchard, hawthorn just about everywhere and carpets of bluebells on the Graig.</p>\r\n              <p>Have a BBQ in the orchard; watch the bats feeding at dusk, listen out for owls and enjoy a spot of star gazing.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n          <div class="panel-heading">\r\n            <h2>Summer</h2>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="panel-body">\r\n            <div class="panel-body"><img src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/summer.jpg" alt="Summer at Trevyr" class="img-responsive img-left" />\r\n              <p>Wander down to the village, 20 minutes'' walk away. Explore the castle and visit our medieval church.</p>\r\n              <p>Cycle to Skenfrith and take a dip in the River Monnow by the castle green.</p>\r\n              <p>Check out the local <a href="http://www.festivalsinmonmouthshire.co.uk" target="_blank">festival calendar</a>, or visit one of the many traditional village fun days.</p>\r\n              <p>Plan a picnic with fruit from the orchard and fresh produce from our vegetable plot.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n          <div class="panel-heading">\r\n            <h2>Autumn</h2>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="panel-body">\r\n            <div class="panel-body"><img src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/autumn.jpg" alt="Autumn in Trevyr" class="img-responsive img-left" />\r\n              <p>Enjoy walnuts, or hazlenuts from our trees (if you can beat the squirrels). Enjoy the autumn colours up on the hills.</p>\r\n              <p>Go foraging for blackberries and other hedgerow fruits on the Graig.</p>\r\n              <p><a href="activities.html" target="_blank">Cycle</a> the Four Castles or the Sustrans trail from Abergavenny to Brynmawr.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <div class="panel panel-default">\r\n          <div class="panel-heading">\r\n            <h2>Winter</h2>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class="panel-body">\r\n            <div class="panel-body"><img src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/winter.jpg" alt="Winter in Trevyr" class="img-responsive img-left" />\r\n              <p>If we get snow, make sure you bring a sledge and check out our slopes.</p>\r\n              <p>Walk down to the village and sit by the log fire in the Angel Inn with a newspaper and a glass of real ale or local cider.</p>\r\n              <p>Pick up some great <a href="foodAndDrink.html" target="_blank">local produce</a> and cook up a feast.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>', 'Seasonal', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '76-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-15 15:58:57', '2016-10-15 15:58:57', '', 76, 'http://localhost:81/wordpress-trevrybarn/76-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(369, 1, '2016-10-15 16:10:13', '2016-10-15 16:10:13', ' <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h1 class="brand-name text-center">Food, drink & dining guide</h1>\r\n        <hr />\r\n        <p>Abergavenny is the home of the famous annual Food and Drink Festival, held every September. This attracts world famous chefs demonstrating their cooking skills and inspiring their audiences.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h2>Restaurants</h2>\r\n        <p>Monmouthshire is rightly famous for extending a hospitable welcome to all visitors and for the fabulous food on offer. The following restaurants are only a short distance from Trevyr Barn:</p>\r\n        <ul class="list-inline text-center largerList">\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thewalnuttreeinn.com/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">The\r\n            Walnut Tree, Llandewi Skirrid</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thehardwick.co.uk/" title="Pub and restaurant ">The\r\n            Hardwick</a></li>\r\n<p>https://css-tricks.com/snippets/wordpress/remove-paragraph-tags-from-around-images/</p>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://toietmoi.co.uk/" title="Pub and restaurant ">Toi Et Moi</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <ul class="list-inline text-center largerList">\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.18-61.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">1861, Cross\r\n            Ash</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thestonemill.co.uk/home/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">Stone Mill</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://angelhotelabergavenny.com/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">The\r\n            Angel, Abergavenny</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.skenfrith.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n            Bell at Skenfrith</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"><img class="img-responsive img-border pull-right" src="img/food01.jpg" alt="Grosmont, The Angel Pub" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>Friendly local Pubs</h2>\r\n        <p> In the centre of <a href="http://www.grosmont.org/">Grosmont</a> village is <a href="http://www.grosmont.org/group/the-angel-inn" target="_blank" title="Pub and Restaurant">The Angel Inn</a>, our friendly local,\r\n          offering lunches and evening meals and a great selection of local ales\r\n          and ciders.</p>\r\n        <p> Other local pubs offering great food and drink include: <a href="http://www.garwaymooninn.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n          Moon at Garway</a>, <a href="http://www.hunters-moon-inn.co.uk/">The Hunter''s Moon</a> at Llangatock Lingoed, <a href="http://cottageofcontent.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant"> The\r\n          Cottage of Content</a> (Carey), <a href="http://www.thecrownatpantygelli.com/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n          Crown</a> at Pantygelli and the <a href="http://www.bridgeinnkentchurch.co.uk/">Bridge Inn</a> at Kentchurch.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"> <img class="img-responsive img-border img-left" src="img/local-produce.jpg" alt="A selection of local produce" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>Food shopping</h2>\r\n        <p>Monmouth is justly proud of the fantastic food and drink produced locally. We hope that our visitors will enjoy sampling what''s on offer.  The <a href="http://www.madeinmonmouthshire.com" target="_blank" title="Made in Monmouthshire">Made in Monmouthshire</a> website provides plenty of information about local producers of food, drink, arts and crafts.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>', 'Food, Drink and Dining', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-15 16:10:13', '2016-10-15 16:10:13', '', 78, 'http://localhost:81/wordpress-trevrybarn/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(370, 1, '2016-10-15 16:11:52', '2016-10-15 16:11:52', ' <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h1 class="brand-name text-center">Food, drink & dining guide</h1>\r\n        <hr />\r\n        <p>Abergavenny is the home of the famous annual Food and Drink Festival, held every September. This attracts world famous chefs demonstrating their cooking skills and inspiring their audiences.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h2>Restaurants</h2>\r\n        <p>Monmouthshire is rightly famous for extending a hospitable welcome to all visitors and for the fabulous food on offer. The following restaurants are only a short distance from Trevyr Barn:</p>\r\n        <ul class="list-inline text-center largerList">\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thewalnuttreeinn.com/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">The\r\n            Walnut Tree, Llandewi Skirrid</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thehardwick.co.uk/" title="Pub and restaurant ">The\r\n            Hardwick</a></li>\r\n<p>https://css-tricks.com/snippets/wordpress/remove-paragraph-tags-from-around-images/</p>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://toietmoi.co.uk/" title="Pub and restaurant ">Toi Et Moi</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <ul class="list-inline text-center largerList">\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.18-61.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">1861, Cross\r\n            Ash</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.thestonemill.co.uk/home/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">Stone Mill</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://angelhotelabergavenny.com/" target="_blank" title="Restaurant">The\r\n            Angel, Abergavenny</a></li>\r\n          <span class = "glyphicon glyphicon-star hidden-xs"></span>\r\n          <li><a href="http://www.skenfrith.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n            Bell at Skenfrith</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"><img class="img-responsive img-border pull-right" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/food01.jpg" alt="Grosmont, The Angel Pub" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>Friendly local Pubs</h2>\r\n        <p> In the centre of <a href="http://www.grosmont.org/">Grosmont</a> village is <a href="http://www.grosmont.org/group/the-angel-inn" target="_blank" title="Pub and Restaurant">The Angel Inn</a>, our friendly local,\r\n          offering lunches and evening meals and a great selection of local ales\r\n          and ciders.</p>\r\n        <p> Other local pubs offering great food and drink include: <a href="http://www.garwaymooninn.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n          Moon at Garway</a>, <a href="http://www.hunters-moon-inn.co.uk/">The Hunter''s Moon</a> at Llangatock Lingoed, <a href="http://cottageofcontent.co.uk/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant"> The\r\n          Cottage of Content</a> (Carey), <a href="http://www.thecrownatpantygelli.com/" target="_blank" title="Pub and restaurant">The\r\n          Crown</a> at Pantygelli and the <a href="http://www.bridgeinnkentchurch.co.uk/">Bridge Inn</a> at Kentchurch.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-4"> <img class="img-responsive img-border img-left" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/local-produce.jpg" alt="A selection of local produce" /> </div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n        <h2>Food shopping</h2>\r\n        <p>Monmouth is justly proud of the fantastic food and drink produced locally. We hope that our visitors will enjoy sampling what''s on offer.  The <a href="http://www.madeinmonmouthshire.com" target="_blank" title="Made in Monmouthshire">Made in Monmouthshire</a> website provides plenty of information about local producers of food, drink, arts and crafts.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>', 'Food, Drink and Dining', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-15 16:11:52', '2016-10-15 16:11:52', '', 78, 'http://localhost:81/wordpress-trevrybarn/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(371, 1, '2016-10-15 16:12:47', '2016-10-15 16:12:47', ' <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box">\r\n      <div class="col-sm-12">\r\n        <h1 class="brand-name text-center">Environment statement</h1>\r\n        <hr />\r\n        <p>We believe that we can manage Trevyr Barn on an environmentally responsible basis, without compromising the luxury of your holiday. These are some of the measures that we have taken:</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="row">\r\n    <div class="box"><div class="col-sm-4"> <img class="img-responsive img-border img-left" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/environment.jpg" alt="Upper Neuadd reservoir Brecon Beacons" />© Crown copyright (2016) Visit Wales</div>\r\n      <div class="col-sm-8">\r\n      <h2>How we help the environment</h2>\r\n        <ul class="tickBullet">\r\n          <li>We optimized the overall energy efficiency rating when we undertook the conversion in 2008 (taking into account the age and construction of the original building).</li>\r\n          <li>The barn is heated by an energy efficient condensing boiler, and we have fitted the latest thermostatic controls to the under floor heating downstairs and the radiators upstairs.</li>\r\n          <li>We use ecologically responsible cleaning products wherever possible.</li>\r\n          <li>Laundry is line dried in the orchard when the weather permits.</li>\r\n          <li>We encourage our guests to recycle; and provide appropriate facilities.</li>\r\n          <li>We are committed to supporting local businesses, and all the services we employ are locally based.</li>\r\n          <li>We believe in minimising food miles and enjoying the fantastic local produce for which Monmouthshire is so well known. Our welcome pack includes a range of locally produced goodies.</li>\r\n          <li>We are members of our local community sustainable agriculture project and have recently contributed one of our fields to grow fruit and vegetables collectively.</li>\r\n          <li>Trevyr used to have a cider mill and our orchard has a range of traditional fruit trees which haven''t seen a pesticide for years, if ever. You are welcome to help yourself to fruit in season.</li>\r\n          <li>There is some fantastic walking and cycling to be enjoyed, and we encourage our guests to get out and enjoy the area.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      \r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>', 'Environment', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '93-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-15 16:12:47', '2016-10-15 16:12:47', '', 93, 'http://localhost:81/wordpress-trevrybarn/93-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
