(378, 1, '2016-10-23 08:50:39', '2016-10-23 08:50:39', '<div class="row">\n<div class="box">\n<div class="col-sm-12">\n<h1 class="brand-name text-center">History &amp; culture get stuffed</h1>\n<h2>[insert_php]\necho ''<p>Hello World</p>'';\n[insert_php]</h2>\n<hr />\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="row">\n<div class="box">\n<div class="col-sm-4"><img class="img-responsive img-border" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/Trevyr_20080514_0062.jpg" alt="Grosmont Church" /></div>\n<div class="col-sm-8">\n<h2>The Welsh borders</h2>\nThe Welsh borders have seen many of the famous and infamous episodes of British history. These have left a legacy of castles, churches and other historical sites across the local area:\n<div id="copybullets" class="wide">\n<ul>\n 	<li>The Three Castles – Grosmont, Skenfrith, White Castle</li>\n 	<li><a href="http://www.caerleon.net/" target="blank">Roman site at Caerleon</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/raglan.html" target="blank">Raglan Castle</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="http://www.herefordcathedral.org/" target="blank">Hereford Cathedral (home of Mappa Mundi)</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/llantho.html" target="blank">Llanthony Abbey</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="http://www.castlewales.com/tintern.html" target="blank">Tintern Abbey</a></li>\n 	<li><a href="http://visitblaenavon.mobi/" target="blank">Blaenavon - World Heritage site (Industrial Revolution and Big Pit)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="row">\n<div class="box">\n<div class="col-sm-4"><img class="img-responsive img-border" src="[insert_php] bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); [/insert_php]/images/trevyr_092203_0027.jpg" alt="Skenfrith Castle" /></div>\n<div class="col-sm-8">\n<h2>Walking, History &amp; culture</h2>\nWhy not combine a little walking and some history? Trevyr Barn is a stone''s throw from Offa''s Dyke and in the middle of the 32 km Three Castles walk (Grosmont, White Castle and Skenfrith) which, for the fit, can be completed in a long summer''s day. There are plenty of shorter variations, and we will be happy to help you plan.\n\nIn <a href="http://www.grosmont.org" target="blank">Grosmont</a>, St Nicolas Church, with its large medieval nave, was built in the 13th Century as part of the supporting infrastructure for Grosmont Castle. There are plenty of other interesting churches nearby, and among the best are: Cwmyoy, Partrishow, Kilpeck and Abbey Dore.\n\nThe Village Alive Trust is a local charity which works to preserve our local heritage and history. It has restored some fascinating buildings and has created some short trails to help you explore. Check out their website <a title="Village Alive Trust" href="http://www.villagealivetrust.org.uk" target="_blank">here</a>.\n\n<a href="http://www.hayfestival.com/wales" target="blank">The Hay Literary Festival</a> is an internationally renowned cultural event. Throughout the year, there are plenty of local festivals to suit all interests, which celebrate the culture and heritage of Monmouthshire. Check <a title="Festivals in Monmouthshire" href="http://www.festivalsinmonmouthshire.co.uk/index.html" target="_blank">here</a> for some ideas.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'History and Culture', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '74-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-10-23 08:50:39', '2016-10-23 08:50:39', '', 74, 'http://localhost:81/wp_trevyrbarn/2016/10/23/74-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
